OK, that all sounds
well and good.

01:12:12.240 --> 01:12:13.800
They have 100% here.

01:12:13.800 --> 01:12:16.040
As we bring in our
key employees-- here

01:12:16.040 --> 01:12:18.410
we have a VP of
R&amp;D. He's critical.

01:12:18.410 --> 01:12:22.580
Normally, you'd say a VP
of R&amp;D would get about 1%.

01:12:22.580 --> 01:12:26.550
Well, in reality, by the
time we get out to this,

01:12:26.550 --> 01:12:29.590
after all of our dilution
out here, this VP of R&amp;D

01:12:29.590 --> 01:12:31.290
is going to be at 1%.

01:12:34.270 --> 01:12:36.270
And some other key
employees here.

01:12:36.270 --> 01:12:39.080
And maybe a board of
advisors or board members,

01:12:39.080 --> 01:12:40.680
who would get some equity.

