01:16:44.340 --> 01:16:48.800
I saved my founders
by thinking ahead

01:16:48.800 --> 01:16:51.960
about what we needed to do.

01:16:51.960 --> 01:16:58.300
So I saved my salary and
equity for him, you know,

01:16:58.300 --> 01:17:00.860
10 times over.

01:17:00.860 --> 01:17:01.870
But we did have a deal.

01:17:01.870 --> 01:17:04.520
For the very first
year, I worked half time

01:17:04.520 --> 01:17:06.060
for half salary.

01:17:06.060 --> 01:17:11.840
And then, we agreed that as the
company-- I was in a position

01:17:11.840 --> 01:17:13.260
where I could work half time.

01:17:13.260 --> 01:17:16.080
And so I think it's
good to have-- maybe you

01:17:16.080 --> 01:17:21.560
have a mentor advisor for that
first year and a controller.

01:17:21.560 --> 01:17:26.210
But the problem is, is that
you really want someone,

01:17:26.210 --> 01:17:28.260
especially when you
start raising money,

01:17:28.260 --> 01:17:31.710
you want someone who's been
through the process before.

01:17:31.710 --> 01:17:36.510
And they will save
you-- you know,

01:17:36.510 --> 01:17:41.080
an experienced person will
save you a couple percent

01:17:41.080 --> 01:17:43.100
of dilution right off the bat.

